item.title: ICM QUALITY MIX - Vol.155 MEOW WOLF RADIO TAVE
item.description:
Meow Wolf's Radio Tave in Houston is an immersive, sound-driven art experience where visitors explore a surreal, multidimensional radio station (ETNL) pulled from reality, featuring hidden portals to strange realms like a cosmic cavern, a surreal house party, and a cowboy dive bar (Cowboix Hevvven). It blends local Houston culture with Meow Wolf's signature interactive storytelling, allowing guests to wander through dozens of rooms, discover hidden lore, interact with musical elements, and uncover secrets tied to the larger Meow Wolf universe. I’ll be honest, it’s been an incredibly tough year. Our family hasn’t been in a particularly festive mood going into the holidays, but we still have a strong affinity for music, color, and art. Meow Wolf Radio Tave was just what the doctor ordered. -Meta

item.title: I'm so proud of him
item.description: I know it might seem like a silly thing to share but my dad was the reason I got into gaming in the first place. We've played so many games together. Some of my fondest memories were of playing co-op games to completion like Battletech (Genesis) Resistance: Fall of Man (PS3) Army of Two (PS3) and more. After he had his stroke back in 2018, I was afraid it would stop him from gaming entirely. So I was more than a little surprised when he got Armored Core VI on his own volition recently. I was worried that such a fast paced game would be too much for him but he never gave up. He threw himself at it and kept trying and dying and trying over and over until he finally beat it. I'm so proud of my Dad. T.T

item.title: QuackFamily Update - Sickness for Christmas
item.description:
It has been a doooozy the past few days. Jasmne has been sick so we're trying to get her in with our local vet as soon as we can. She still loves to cuddle, so we are hoping for the best.
Teddy and Baby Dragon have slowing become friends. Baby Dragon is still getting over her upper respiratory infection but she is gaining strength each day.
Peppercorn came down with a sickness as well. We had a traveling vet that came by. He has an inner ear infection. I've been giving him water and vitamins via drops. Only time will tell if the antibiotics will help
But let's get to the happiest moments. We decorated our tree for Baby Dragon. She absolutely adored everything.
We have portraits of Angel Food Cake and Teddy Game done by a good friend of ours.
Another friend of ours made this absolutely adorable felt corgi ornament.
Our inlaws also had this adorable Pikachu ornament added as well! We always love adding things to our tree and more. If you would like to send us artwork or drawings, feel free to let me know. I've loved everything.
